formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. We have relied on management representation for issuance of this certificate. 2. For coherence point in this certificate we have relied on the management representation and we have applied to the best of our prudence to judge actual progress of the building at site. 
3. Previous owner of land has obtained development rights on land in his name and all the expenses related to development was incurred by him. After that promoter has purchased land with all rights and amount was paid for land. So, there are no separate develpoment expenses for project is incurred by the promoter. Hence, no amount is shown as point 1.b of land cost. (as per land purchase deed). 4. For 23 booked units cash amount Rs. 10,000/- per unit is received as consideration as per banakhat. Cash receipt is not deposited in RERA Account. Hence, full amount Rs. 2,30,000/- is considered as withdrawal for this certificate. 5. Promter has deposited amount received through cheque/online transfer in RERA Account instead of depositing in Collection Account. So, 100% amount is deposited in RERA Account.
